The business management system of record for hybrid IT
 
Apptio's SaaS applications transform the way IT runs its business and makes decisions.
 
See Products
Light GrayBackground Image: default-padding bgs-coverbgp-tcbot-pad-text-onlytop-pad-defaultbg-gray-dark 01




default-padding Apptio is built for you
With our cloud-based applications, IT and finance leaders manage, plan, and optimize their technology investments across on-premises and cloud. Here's how our products empower technology business leaders:
WhiteBackground Image: 0bg-gray-lightest 0top-pad-halfbgs-coverbgp-bcbot-pad-tiny










Office of the CIO







IT Finance







Infrastructure & Ops



0Office of the CIOWith Apptio, CIOs get full visibility into IT costs to make fact-based technology decisions that deliver business value.Proactively manage IT spend to budget and make informed staffing decisions.
Understand infrastructure cost & trends, prioritize public cloud decisions, and manage application portfolio for business value.

Align project resources to business priorities and drive shared accountability of IT costs with the BU.

Learn more 


0IT FinanceFrom setting budgets to analyzing and managing spend, Apptio streamlines financial management for IT.Proactively manage IT spend by identifying variances to budget and plan, and make course corrections.
Improve forecast accuracy by collaborating with budget owners to get up-to-date spending information.
Create an accurate annual budget and plan based on true IT cost drivers and resources vs top-down estimates.
Learn more 


0Infrastructure & Operations LeadersApptio enables IT leaders to manage, plan, and optimize their technology investments across on-premise and public cloud services.Get full transparency into public cloud spend to optimize cloud purchasing and usage.
Make informed decisions about how to best optimize cost and usage across hybrid IT resources.
Influence demand of hybrid IT investments to better plan for and manage supply and drive adoption.
Learn more 






Office of the CIO

































IT Finance






























Infrastructure / Operations




























