Apptio, Inc. Key Developments

Apptio, Inc. Appoints Kathleen Philips as Director
Jun 1 17
On May 31, 2017, the Board of Directors of Apptio, Inc. increased the size of the Board to eight directors, and appointed Kathleen Philips to serve as a director of the company, with the appointment effective immediately. Ms. Philips has been with Zillow Group, Inc. since 2010, and has served as Zillow Group's chief financial officer and treasurer since August 2015, chief legal officer since September 2014, and secretary since July 2010. Ms. Philips has also been appointed to serve on the Audit Committee and Compensation Committee of the Company.


Apptio, Inc. Selected As One Of Seven Cloud Service Providers for FedRAMP Connect Program
May 17 17
Apptio Inc. announced that one of seven cloud service providers selected for the FedRAMP Connect program. Through participation in this program, Apptio will be prioritized for FedRAMP certification based on demand from CIOs across the Federal government. FedRAMP Connect is a new initiative developed by FedRAMP working closely with the Federal CIO Council and OMB. Of the 40 vendors that applied for FedRAMP Connect, only seven were selected based on their government-wide demand, applicability for cross-agency use, and the security of their system. The Federal Risk and Authorization Management Program (FedRAMP), is a government-wide program that provides a standardized approach to security assessment, authorization, and continuous monitoring for cloud products and services.


Apptio, Inc. Presents at 45th Annual J.P. Morgan Global Technology, Media and Telecom Conference, May-23-2017 10:40 AM
May 16 17
Apptio, Inc. Presents at 45th Annual J.P. Morgan Global Technology, Media and Telecom Conference, May-23-2017 10:40 AM. Venue: Westin Copley Place, 10 Huntington Ave., Boston, Massachusetts, United States. Speakers: Sachin Gupta, Co-Founder, Chief Executive Officer, President and Director.


